MIAMI, March 2—A colt bred only about 50 miles from New York is the strong favorite to take the Flamingo Stakes to morrow. The Elberon Farm's Silent Screen, foaled at the Tilly Foster stock farm in Brewster, N. Y., is expected to be the odds‐on choice against a dozen rivals in the colorful contest for 3‐year‐olds at Hia leah. Listed for its 41st run ning, this Flamingo will be the richest in history, its gross value with 13 starters amount ing to $161,400. To the winner will go $104,910, a sum that has been exceeded twice in the past. View Full Article in Timesmachine »